                     <interp inst="def1-2568-18430821" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM SMITH</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18430821-2568-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18430821-2568-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18430821-2568-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18430821-cd-306" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430821-2568-offence-1 t18430821-cd-306"></join>15th of August</rs>, 1 coat, value 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18430821-name-1760" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1760" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1760" type="surname" value="HARRIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1760" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430821-2568-offence-1 t18430821-name-1760"></join>George Harris</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1761" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1761" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1761" type="surname" value="HARRIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1761" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE HARRIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at Tunbridge, in Kent. On the 15th of August I was at the Catherine Wheel, in the Borough—I had a coat there, which I</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184308210232"></xptr>
               <p>saw safe in the van in the yard, at a quarter to six o'clock in the morning, under the seat—I missed it at half-past six—this now produced is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1762" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1762" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1762" type="surname" value="BURFIN,"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1762" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BURFIN, JUN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am "boots" at the Catherine Wheel. I saw the prisoner come away from the van, with the coat under his arm, that morning—I gave information to the constable.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1763" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1763" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1763" type="surname" value="BURFIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1763" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BURFIN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a watchman. I was sent for, and spoke to the prisoner about the coat—he said he had not seen any coat—I said I insisted on his telling me where it was—he immediately said it was in the parlour—he went into the parlour, and pulled it from under the seat.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I intended going to Tunbridge Wells that day, and thought the van started at seven o'clock, instead of which, it was nine; I sat down in the parlour; two persons came in; I went to the water-closet at the end of the yard; there was a man there; I waited two or three minute, till he came out; I then went in, and found the coat there; I brought it out on my arm, carried it directly to the parlour, and <hi rend="italic">chucked</hi> it on the seat; I then came and stood at the door till the watchman came and asked about it; I said, "I have got no coat, there is one on the seat;" if I intended to steal it I should have taken it away.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1764" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1764" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1764" type="surname" value="BURFIN,"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1764" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BURFIN, JUN</persName>
                  </hi>. <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> When I first saw him he had the coat under his arm—I afterwards saw him with it on his back, underneath his own—I went to fetch a policeman—he was going from the van, towards the water-closet.</p>
               <p>
